headline: The Trump Administration Is Ending Private Medicare’s Cost Crisis. Humana, CVS Stock Jump.
summary: The Trump administration just rescued the big health insurers with a $25 billion payout.  For more than a year, the story for these companies has been that the business of privately managing Medicare plans had become a major disappointment.  U.S. seniors were seeking lots of medical care, eating away at insurers’ profits.

headline: Insurance stocks, Levi's outlook, Super Micro pops: Market Minute
summary: Brad Smith outlines some of the top headlines investors need to know on Market Minute. Healthcare stocks like Humana (HUM), UnitedHealth (UNH), and CVS (CVS) rise after the US boosts Medicare reimbursement rates. Levi Strauss (LEVI) stock is in focus after the company maintained its full-year outlook and said it expects "minimal impact" from tariffs in the upcoming quarter. Super Micro Computer (SMCI) extends gains after being the top performer in the S&P 500 (^GSPC) during Monday's session. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Health insurance stocks soar after boost to Medicare reimbursement rates
summary: Shares of U.S. health insurers jumped on Tuesday after a bigger-than-expected increase in the government's reimbursement rates for Medicare Advantage plans in 2026 signaled some relief for a sector burdened with steep medical costs.  Shares of Medicare-focused insurer Humana led gains with a nearly 15% jump in premarket trading, while other health insurers including UnitedHealth Group, Centene and CVS Health advanced between 5% and 9%.  The "best-case scenario" rates, coupled with rising tariff risk, make health insurance stocks a strong relative safe haven, Baird Research analysts said in a note to clients.
